choices.text:
to ride a donkey. One day we were walking back from the grocery store, we heard some donkey hooves behind us. I turned around to have a bit of a laugh only to see that the beast was pulling a cart with two cows in front and a couple of goats in the back. When we turned down a different road I figured that we had lost the donkey man but to our surprise he was still on our tail. The biggest lesson I learned in Lesotho is how to ride a donkey. I was so embarrassed to be caught on a donkey that I told everyone that I was riding because my legs were sore from a 5km walk. I swear I will report this back home so people will believe me.

This site has photos and more information about Lesotho.

-Lindsey
